headlines.description: — Moritz Wagner scored a season-high 26 points, younger brother Franz added 19 points and seven assists, and the Orlando Magic beat the Charlotte Hornets 116-109 on Friday night to snap a 10-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wagner brothers, Magic top Hornets to end 10-game skid

headlines.description: — Trey Lyles scored 21 points, Cade Cunningham and Hamidou Diallo each added 18 and the Detroit Pistons extending their surprising stretch by beating the Toronto Raptors 103-87 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons ride strong bench to 103-87 victory over Raptors

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 35 points, Deandre Ayton had 27 points and 12 rebounds and the NBA-leading Phoenix Suns beat the Indiana Pacers 112-94 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Ayton help NBA-leading Suns beat Pacers, 112-94

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 25 points and 13 rebounds and the Philadelphia 76ers used a dominating start to roll to a 111-99 victory over the Boston Celtics on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid has 25 points and 13 rebounds, 76ers beat Celtics

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Chicago Bulls

headlines.description: — The Golden State Warriors were in a rut and in need of a breather. They sure got one.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors roll to most lopsided win, beat Bulls 138-96

headlines.description: — The stars were out in Miami. Drake was sitting courtside. Golfer Brooks Koepka had prime seats.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat rally late, scramble to get past Hawks, 124-118

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 32 points and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat San Antonio 114-109 on Friday night, extending the Spurs’ losing streak to five.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland, Allen lead Cavaliers past struggling Spurs, 114-109

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 27 points, 12 rebounds and 10 assists in his 40th career triple-double, and the Dallas Mavericks used a second-half rally to rout Memphis 112-85 on Friday night and end the Grizzlies’ winning streak at 11 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mavs rout Grizzlies 112-85, ending Memphis' winning streak

headlines.description: — Marvin Bagley III had season highs of 26 points and 13 rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Houston Rockets 126-114 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bagley's breakout game leads Kings past Rockets, 126-115
